### Quick User API Tests
### Make sure your backend is running on http://localhost:3000

### 1. Register a new user
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "User"
}

### 2. Login to get token
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Get user profile (replace TOKEN with actual token)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/users/profile/me
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN

### 4. Get all users (admin only - replace ADMIN_TOKEN)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/users
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_TOKEN

### 5. Create user (admin only - replace ADMIN_TOKEN)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/users
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_TOKEN

{
  "username": "newuser",
  "email": "newuser@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "USER",
  "firstName": "New",
  "lastName": "User"
} 